}
```
This interface violates Interface Segregation Principle (ISP) as it has too many methods, some of which are not used by any class implementing this interface. The ISP suggests that clients should be able to depend on the smallest possible interfaces. In this case, we can refactor the `MusicPlayer` interface into smaller ones like:
```java
