        result = low_level.operation(data)
        return result
```
This class violates Dependency Inversion Principle (DIP) because it has high-level modules depending on low-level modules directly which is not good for decoupling the software components and making them independent of each other. It should depend on abstractions instead of concretions.

**Code Rating: 1.5 out of 5 (SRP, OCP, LSP, ISP, DIP)**

Refactoring would involve splitting `UserManager` into smaller classes with single responsibility each and making the high-level module depend on abstractions instead of concretions. The refactored code will be more complex but it adheres to SOLID principles better. 

